This clarifies the brand architecture perfectly: Powerstarter Hub is the flagship "front-of-house" portal where the world (Collaborators, 
Contractors, and Backers) interacts, while Powerframe is the "industrial-strength" backbone and engine room running under the hood.
Here is how we restructure the engineering and creative link to fit this WOMmedia Group vision.

1. The Powerstarter Hub (The Destination)
This is your Social-Engineering Platform. It serves as the primary URL where business projects are "upskilled."
The Interface: An Instagram-style "RootJournal" feed for project achievements.
The Hub Features: A "Join as Collaborator" button, a "Bounty Board" for Contractors, and a "Back this Project" gateway for investors.
The Link: It pulls 2D/3D assets from Mucho3D and technical "proof of progress" from Powerframe.

2. The Powerframe (The Backbone)
This is the Application Infrastructure. It stays invisible to the casual user but handles the heavy lifting.
The Logic: It contains the @trt/logic (Achievement thresholds) and the @trt/db (The source of truth for metrics and finances).
Connectivity: It manages the GitHub API links and ensures that a "Commit" in a sub-repo triggers a "Milestone" in the Powerstarter Hub.
Hosting: It runs on Coolify, serving the Unity WebGL builds and the BMS data streams to your CM4 Hand Terminal.

3. Integrated Action Plan: Building the Hub
Use this prompt to align the repos into this new Hub-Backbone relationship:
Role: Lead Enterprise Architect for WOMmedia Group.
Task: Establish the Powerstarter Hub as the primary collaboration platform, powered by the Powerframe backbone.
Requirements:
Backbone Linkage: Configure Powerframe to act as a multi-tenant API. It must be able to ingest data from multiple project repos and output them as "Achievement Posts" on the Powerstarter Hub.
Stakeholder Portal: Create the "Colab/Hire/Back" logic within Powerstarter:
Collaborators: Link GitHub PRs to "Contributor Badges" on the Hub.
Contractors: Link Mucho3D asset approvals to "Bounty Payouts" managed by Powerframe.
Backers: Create a "Premium View" that shows live Unity 3D previews (Upskilled visuals) only to project backers.
The Engineering-Art Bridge: Ensure that any 3D UI/UX file uploaded to Mucho3D is automatically "vetted" by Powerframe's technical scripts before it appears on the Powerstarter Hub feed.
Goal: Create a high-trust, functional environment where professional art engineering is the main value driver for business projects.

4. Why this is the "Steady Work Environment"
For the Artist: They work in Mucho3D, seeing their work live in the "Powerstarter" browser view immediately.
For the Developer: They work in Powerframe or a linked project repo, knowing their code triggers the "Achievements."
For the Client: They visit the Powerstarter Hub to see their project being "Upskilled" in real-time by WOMmedia's elite talent.
The CM4 "Master Key"
Your CM4 Handheld will run a specialized version of the Powerstarter Hub. It will be the only device that has "Admin" rights to release payments
to contractors and "Verify" milestones before they go public on the hub.
Should we start by building the "Stakeholder Dashboard" in Powerstarter Hub, or the "Multi-Tenant Logic" in the Powerframe backbone?

