This is a high-level Enterprise Architecture roadmap. You are shifting from building "apps" to building an Industrial Operating System for the WOMmedia Group.
By evolving these three repositories separately before adding the Azure LLM Orchestrator, you ensure the AI agent has "clean data" to act upon. Without structured repositories, a CLI agent 
is just a chatbot; with them, it becomes a Digital Project Manager.
Here is the evolution plan for your three core repositories:

1. Powerframe BMS (The Engineering Heart)
Current: Hardware/Battery metrics and 5-point plans.
Evolution: It becomes the Project Blueprint Engine.
The Upgrade: It must link raw engineering plans to real-time hardware readiness. It provides the "Technical Source of Truth."
Role: If the BMS says a system isn't stable, the entire project status in the Hub reflects this risk.

2. Powerframe CRM ➔ BME (The Business Mind)
Current: Customer Relationship Management.
Evolution: Upgraded to a Business Management Environment (BME).
Product Monitoring: Instead of just tracking "customers," it monitors "product details." It tracks the ROI, the cost per 3D asset from Mucho3D, and the time-to-market for each feature.
Collaboration Hub: This is where project repo data (GitHub connectivity) is displayed. It shows the status of 2D/3D UI/UX files and links them to the business goals.
Deployment Monitor: It tracks the real-time status of web domains on Vercel or other hosting platforms.

3. Powerframe Hub (The Bridge & Marketplace)
Current: Infrastructure backbone.
Evolution: The Consolidated Multi-Tenant Portal.
The Ingestor: It bridges the live feed from the TRT App (the Instagram-style achievements) into the business dashboards.
Mucho3D Integration: This is the primary platform for hiring. It connects the "Need" (from the BME) to the "Talent" (from Mucho3D).
The Command Console: It provides the unified view. A stakeholder logs in and sees: Code Status (GitHub) + Visual Status (Mucho3D) + Tech Status (BMS) + Financial Status (BME).
Phase 1 Action: The "Structural Alignment" Prompt
Before building the Azure LLM, use this prompt to synchronize the three repos:
Role: Enterprise Systems Architect.
Task: Align the Powerframe BMS, BME, and Hub repositories into a unified ecosystem for WOMmedia Group.
1. BMS (Project Detail Linker): Implement a ProjectMaster schema that links 5-point engineering plans to live hardware telemetry.
2. BME (Business Environment): Expand the current CRM into a Product Monitor. Integrate the GitHub API to track the progress of specific 2D/3D assets and display their "Deployment Status" (Vercel/Live).
3. The Hub (The Bridged Connector): Build the integration layer that pulls the TRT App Feed and maps it to the Mucho3D Hiring System.
Goal: Ensure every repository uses a mutual ProjectID so that the LLM Orchestrator can later navigate the entire project route via a single CLI interface.
The Future: The Azure LLM Orchestrator
Once these three are stable, the Azure LLM acts as the CLI Agent. You will be able to type: "Agent, what is the current bottleneck in Project X?"
The AI will check the BMS (for tech blocks), the BME (for budget/hiring blocks), and the Hub (for creative blocks) to give you a perfect answer.
Should we start by defining the "Shared Project Schema" in Prisma to link the BME and BMS together in the Hub?
